item.title: Compiler Errors!
item.dc:creator: @SirPali SirPali
item.description:
@SirPali wrote:

Already defined means you have declared something (in this case, the ints and some methods) twice.

The symbol-errors mean you are trying to use a method that does not exist. In this case that would be TeleportToX, TeleportToY, and sendMessage.

Try changing TeleportToY to toY (watch the caps),
TeleportToX to toX,
and sendMessage to sM.

Atleast, I think you’re working with the base I gave you right? If so, change the things I just said and it should work like a charm.

Read full topic
